Lee Fierro, best known as Alex Kintner’s mom in Steven Spielberg’s 1975 shark attack classic “Jaws,” died Sunday of complications from the coronavirus.
The actress was residing at an assisted living facility in Ohio when she died from COVID-19, the Martha’s Vineyard Times reports.
In her iconic scene from “Jaws,” an enraged Fierro confronts Chief Martin Brody (Roy Scheider) and slaps him in the face.
My boy is dead.”Nicki Galland, a novelist who credits Fierro for inspiring her creativity, told the Martha’s Vineyard outlet that Fierro “was tickled by [her cult film notoriety].
A small service is planned by her family in Ohio with a memorial service in Martha’s Vineyard at a later date, Deadline reports.